The paper focuses on object-aware guidance for mobile robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of computer vision techniques for scene reconstruction and understanding suggests that it could also be classified under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a method for autonomous exploration and reconstruction, which involves decision-making and planning, indicating that it could also be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of machine learning techniques for object detection and classification suggests that it could also be classified under machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes a method for autonomous navigation, which involves control and optimization, indicating that it could also be classified under control systems (cs.SY).
